channel.title: [PI] Removing CastleWars Doors [PI]
channel.description:
Hey I need help removing the castlewars doors on project insanity base. You can't open them or go through them or anything when you click on them, so I just want them removed.
I've tried going in ObjectManager and deleting them that way, but it won't work?
Please help, thanks

item.dc:creator: @eyeownyew Eyeownyew
item.description:
@eyeownyew wrote:

[quote=“k0 twin, post:4, topic:373884”]try taking the “2” out of objectToRemove();

I seem to remember that being a different method, although I don’t remember what the difference between the two are.[/quote]

One is:

object(objectID, Xcoord, Ycoord, 10, 1);

The other is:

object(objectID, Xcoord, Ycoord, -1, 1);

item.dc:creator: @k0_twin k0 twin
item.description:
@k0_twin wrote:

In your PlayerAssistant.java, under:

public void removeObjects()

add

objectToRemove2(XXXX, YYYY);

Substitute the X’s and Y’s with your doors coordinates.
